South Africa's Faf du Plessis in action. LONDON – South Africa have won the toss and elected to bat first in their crucial World Cup match against India. The Proteas have made two changes to the side lost against Bangladesh. Hashim Amla returns after missing the match against Bangladesh and, with fast bowler Lungi Ngidi injured, the Proteas are playing two spinners. READ: 'Proteas not chokers': Paddy Upton South Africa announced on Tuesday that Dale Steyn had been ruled out of the World Cup without bowling a single ball. The Proteas have lost their first two matches in the tournament while India opens their account. Teams: India: Virat Kohli (capt), Rohit Sharma, Shikhar Dhawan, KL Rahul, Kedar Jadhav, M.S.Dhoni, Hardik Pandya, Bhuvneshwar Kumar, Kuldeep Yadav, Yuzvendra Chahal, Jasprit Bumrah South Africa: Faf du Plessis (capt), Quinton de Kock, Hashim Amla, Rassie van der Dussen, David Miller, JP Duminy, Andile Phehlukwayo, Chris Morris, Kagiso Rabada, Imran Tahir, Tabraiz Shamsi Umpires: Richard Kettleborough (ENG), Michael Gough (ENG) TV Umpire: Richard Illingworth (ENG) Match Referee: Ranjan Madugalle (SRI)  Tweets by OfficialCSA